import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['home_score'].plot.hist(bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Home Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores across all matches?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    avg_home_scores = data.groupby('home_team')['home_score'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = avg_home_scores.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("Which teams have the highest average home scores?")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby('date')['home_score'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data_grouped['date'], data_grouped['home_score'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of home scores over time?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Date")
    plt.ylabel("Average Home Score")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
